Section 1:
1 L.D. 1877
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 JUDICIARY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1248, L.D. 1877, “An Act to Increase
10 Penalties for Human Trafficking Offenses”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of sections 2 to 9.
12 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
13 number to read consecutively.
14 SUMMARY
1155 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, removes the provisions
1166 of the bill that establish mandatory minimum jail sentences, mandatory fines and
1177 mandatory restitution for persons convicted of sex trafficking or aggravated sex trafficking
1188 and removes the requirement for certain professionals to receive human trafficking
1199 awareness training every 2 years. The amendment retains the provision of the bill that
2200 increases the amount a person convicted of sex trafficking or aggravated sex trafficking
2211 must pay to the Victims' Compensation Fund.
2222 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2233 (See attached)
